Introduction

CORBYN, born Cory Hong (Hong Joo-hyun), is a Korean-American singer, songwriter, and producer known for his versatile artistry and innovative music.

First gaining recognition as the leader and main vocalist of the K-pop group 24K, he later launched a solo career in 2019 with his debut single “M$D (Million Dollar Dream).”

Now the executive producer for 28 LABORATORY MUSIC, CORBYN blends pop, R&B, and hip-hop in his work, earning a global fanbase while advocating for mental health awareness and pushing creative boundaries.
